# GitHub Actions minutes

This repo pays for Actions. Prefer **not** triggering CI or Pages for routine designer edits.

## Do not trigger Actions for

- Sidebar property edits (category, variant, source) — commit messages must start with `[skip ci]`
- Staging Contents API commits under `packages/custom-icons/staging/**` (already `paths-ignore`)
- Pure `packages/custom-icons/metadata.json` updates (already `paths-ignore` on CI/Pages)

## Still OK to run Actions for

- Apply staged → library / catalog regeneration
- Real code, tooling, or workflow changes
- Publish / release
- Manual `workflow_dispatch`

## When adding new “everyday” write paths

If you add another Contents API or bot commit that designers hit often (rename metadata, tags, etc.), either:

1. Prefix the commit message with `[skip ci]`, and/or
2. Add the path to `paths-ignore` on `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and `pages.yml`

Do not rely on full CI/Pages to “refresh” property-only catalog fields; Apply and real asset commits already regenerate the catalog.
